PN,41604
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F416A1773155488
OL,3,CTravelodge faces pressure over
OL,4,Csecurity breach after guest sexually
OL,5,Cassaulted
OL,7,FThe assault took place in December
OL,8,F2022 at the Travelodge in Maidenhead.
OL,9,FSmith and the victim had attended the
OL,10,Fsame party before returning to the
OL,11,Fhotel in the early hours.
OL,13,FAt approximately 2am, Smith went to
OL,14,Fthe reception desk and used deception
OL,15,Fto obtain the victim's room key.
OL,17,FNo secondary checks were made with the
OL,18,Fguest before the key was handed over.
OL,19,FThe victim woke up to find Smith
OL,20,Fcarrying out the sexual assault in her
OL,21,Fbed.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G4/8
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,417,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41605
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F416A1773155488
OL,3,CTravelodge faces pressure over
OL,4,Csecurity breach after guest sexually
OL,5,Cassaulted
OL,7,FFollowing a Thames Valley Police
OL,8,Finvestigation, Smith, of London Road,
OL,9,FStaines, was sentenced at Reading
OL,10,FCrown Court to seven years and six
OL,11,Fmonths imprisonment for sexual assault
OL,12,Fand trespass with intent to commit a
OL,13,Fsexual offence.
OL,15,FIn response to a letter from MPs,
OL,16,FTravelodge Chief Executive Jo Boydell
OL,17,Fconfirmed she has written back to the
OL,18,Fgroup and agreed to meet with them.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G5/8
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
